Here are the answers to your two questions:

### Q1. What can you say about these numbers? (unordered set, not a sequence)
178, 200, 146, 174, 124, 166, 132, 134, 140, 182

**Answer:** These are all **even numbers**. Every single number in this set is divisible by 2. Furthermore, they are all 3-digit even numbers, and none of them end in 0 (except 200, which is the only one that does). 

***

### Q2. What can you say about these numbers? (unordered set, not a sequence)
103, 101, 197, 151, 127, 137, 179, 199, 191, 109

**Answer:** These are all **prime numbers**. Every number in this set is a 3-digit prime number, meaning its only divisors are 1 and itself. 

*(Bonus observation: The two sets are clearly related! Set 1 consists of 3-digit even numbers, and Set 2 consists of 3-digit prime numbers.)* [end of text]


